<p><alert>General Form</alert>: In general, the equation of a straight line can be written as</p>
<p><em>ax</em> + <em>by</em> + <em>c</em> = 0,</p>
<p>for constants <em>a</em>, <em>b</em>, <em>c</em> with <em>a</em> and <em>b</em> not both zero. Indeed, if <em>a</em>=0 the line is a horizontal line given by <em>y</em> = −<em>c/b</em>, if <em>b</em>=0 the line is a vertical line given by <em>x</em> = −<em>c/a</em>, and if both <em>a</em>, <em>b≠</em> 0 it is the oblique line given by <em>y</em> = –(<em>a/b)x</em> − <em>c/b</em> with slope <em>m</em> = –<em>a/b</em> and <em>y</em>-intercept −<em>c/b</em> .</p>
