<cell><alert>Definition 4.4</alert>: Let F and F<alert>′</alert> be two fixed points in the plane. An <alert>ellipse</alert> is the locus or set of all points in the plane such that the sum of the distances from each point to F and F<alert>′</alert> is constant. That is, a point P is on the ellipse if and only if |PF|+ |PF<alert>′</alert>| = constant. (See Figure 4.18).</cell>
