<li><p>The longest diameter (longest chord) V<alert>′</alert>V through F<alert>′</alert> and F is called the <alert>major axis</alert> of the ellipse; and the chord BB<alert>′</alert> through C which is perpendicular to V<alert>′</alert>V is called <alert>minor axis</alert>.</p></li>
<li><p>The endpoints of the major axis, V′ and V, are called the <alert>vertices</alert> of the ellipse.</p></li>
</ul>
